  1. Diamond cuts For this problem we will use diamonds data from plotting2 package. If you load the package the data set will be available.
  1. Generate a scatter plot of price vs carat
  2. Color the scatter plot by cut
  3. Show smoothed lines using method ‘loess’
  4. Facet the plot based on clarity
  5. Now generate a side by side boxplot of price by cut. For which cut does the price of diamond appear to be the highest?
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(diamonds, aes(carat, price, color=cut)) + 
  geom_point() + geom_smooth(method="loess") + facet_wrap(~clarity)

ggplot(diamonds, aes(cut, price)) + geom_boxplot()
